    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="557"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/970a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-15T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 15, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. On May 16 Japanese Ambassador handed me a “secret and confidential”
                        memorandum<note n="40" xml:id="d557fn40">For text of memorandum, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_232">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 232</ref>.</note> purporting to
                    represent certain “private thoughts” suggesting that the American and Japanese
                    Governments make a “joint declaration” of policy. On May 29 I informed him
                    orally but definitely that we could not adopt that suggestion. Details follow by
                    pouch.</p>
                <p>On June 13 the Ambassador was received by the President in farewell call. I was
                    present. No matters of policy discussed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
